## Diagnosis

The two-axis grammar (color channel via `border`, weight channel via `ring`) is architecturally correct, but the resting state is painting a 2px border instead of 1px. The border utility being used is almost certainly `border-2` (or a custom token that resolves to `2px`) on the base element, and the engaged state is either inheriting that weight or doubling it via a ring.

---

## Root Cause

**AP-072 ‚Äî Conflating state weight with base weight on interactive primitives.**

The resting border is set to `border-2` when it must be `border` (1px). The engaged ring is correct as an additive paint-only overlay, but because the base is already 2px the resting‚Üíengaged transition reads as 2px‚Üí2px (no perceived change in weight), defeating the two-axis grammar entirely.

---

## Fix

### `components/ui/input.tsx`

```tsx
// BEFORE (incorrect ‚Äî resting border at 2px)
const inputVariants = cva(
  [
    "border-2 border-border",                          // ‚Üê wrong base weight
    "focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring",
    "focus-visible:ring-offset-0",
  ],
  // ...
)

// AFTER ‚Äî resting: 1px hairline; engaged: paint-only 2px ring overlay
const inputVariants = cva(
  [
    // Color channel ‚Äî hairline, always present
    "border border-border",                            // 1px resting

    // Weight channel ‚Äî paint-only ring, no layout shift
    "focus-visible:outline-none",
    "focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring",   // 2px engaged overlay
    "focus-visible:ring-offset-0",                    // flush, no gap artifact

    // Error / invalid state ‚Äî color change only, weight stays at ring-2
    "aria-[invalid=true]:border-destructive",
    "aria-[invalid=true]:focus-visible:ring-destructive",
  ],
  // ...
)
```

### `components/ui/input.tsx` ‚Äî full corrected element

```tsx
<input
  className={cn(
    // Layout & shape
    "flex h-10 w-full rounded-md px-3 py-2",

    // Typography
    "text-sm placeholder:text-muted-foreground",

    // Color channel (resting) ‚Äî 1px hairline
    "border border-border bg-background text-foreground",

    // Weight channel (engaged) ‚Äî 2px ring, paint only
    "focus-visible:outline-none",
    "focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-0",

    // State ‚Äî color only, no weight change
    "aria-[invalid=true]:border-destructive",
    "aria-[invalid=true]:focus-visible:ring-destructive",

    // Interaction
    "disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50",

    className
  )}
  {...props}
/>
```

### `tokens/border.ts` (if the 2px is sourced from a token)

```ts
export const borderTokens = {
  // Structural
  "border-width-resting":  "1px",   // hairline ‚Äî was incorrectly "2px"
  "border-width-engaged":  "2px",   // ring overlay only

  // Map to CSS custom properties
  "--border-resting": "var(--border-width-resting)",
  "--border-engaged":  "var(--border-width-engaged)",
} as const
```

### `tailwind.config.ts` ‚Äî confirm ring is not adding to border

```ts
theme: {
  extend: {
    ringWidth: {
      DEFAULT: "2px",   // engaged weight ‚Äî correct
    },
    borderWidth: {
      DEFAULT: "1px",   // resting weight ‚Äî must be 1px, not 2px
    },
  },
},
```

---

## Axis Table (source of truth)

| State | Color channel (`border`) | Weight channel (`ring`) | Perceived thickness |
|---|---|---|---|
| Resting | `border-border` | none | **1px** |
| Hovered | `border-border/80` | none | 1px |
| Engaged (focus) | `border-ring` | `ring-2 ring-ring` | **2px** |
| Invalid resting | `border-destructive` | none | 1px |
| Invalid engaged | `border-destructive` | `ring-2 ring-destructive` | 2px |

---

## Principle

**Resting state carries zero weight signal.** The 1px hairline communicates affordance through color alone. Weight (2px) is reserved exclusively for the engaged state and is delivered via the paint-only ring so it produces no reflow. Any component that sets `border-2` on a resting interactive primitive violates this grammar ‚Äî the base border utility must always be `border` (1px default).
